{"word":"H8245 - שָׁקַד - shâqad - shaw-kad' - Hasten","slug":"H8245","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">שָׁקַד</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>shâqad"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>shaw-kad'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Hasten"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05E7;&#x05D3; - sha&#x0302;qad</b> - <i>shaw-kad'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be alert</i>, that is, <i>sleepless</i>; hence to <i>be on the lookout</i> (whether for good or ill): - hasten, remain, wake, watch (for)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H8246\">H8246</a>, <a href=\"#/H8247\">H8247</a>"}]}